The paper deals with the design of coded caching schemes, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and combinatorial designs (cs.DS). The focus is on reducing subpacketization, which is a key challenge in coded caching, making cs.SI (signal processing) and cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a technique for constructing new schemes from known ones, which falls under cs.CC (computational complexity).
